===Noun===
'''gousset''' (''plural'' goussets)
#(''Armor'') [[Category:Armor]] A small piece of [[mail]], providing some [[protection]] where two [[plate]]s of armor are [[join]]ed, usually at the [[elbow]]s, under the [[shoulder]]s, and behind the [[knee]]s.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1786''': At the joint, or bending of the arm, the [[vambrace]]s were cut obliquely, the vacancies on the inside, when the arms were [[streighten]]ed, were covered by pieces of mail callet [sic] [[Goussets]], and afterwards by a [[contrivance]] of plates resembling [[heart]]s. &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 22.
